A structured threat assessment of university academic and administrative 
systems using STRIDE, MITRE ATT&CK, and NIST SP 800-30 methodology.

## Key Facts
- 15 threats identified (5 Critical, 8 High, 2 Medium)
- Framework: STRIDE + MITRE ATT&CK + NIST SP 800-30
- Risk Method: Likelihood × Impact Matrix (5×5)

## Assets Assessed
- Student Information System (SIS)
- Learning Management System (LMS)
- Administrative Database
- Campus WiFi Infrastructure
- VPN Gateway & Admin Console

## Top Threats
- Unauthorized Remote Access (No MFA/VPN)
- SQL Injection on Student Portal
- Insider Threat — Data Exfiltration
- Ransomware via Phishing Email
- DDoS on Online Exam Platform

> All scenarios are hypothetical, created for academic purposes.
